{"type":"message","id":"925ced6c","parentId":"dccf6090","timestamp":"2026-03-24T17:06:37.896Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_fnwu67gm2hh0_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 130514\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\n\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine what concrete action to take.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals:\r\n1. Phase 0 and Phase 1 are marked complete\r\n2. Recent work on CFI Compression showed promising results\r\n3. Key finding: Need THREE-DIMENSIONAL filter: CFI ≥ 0.5 AND freq ∈ [3, 120)\r\n4. Next experiment: Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring vs binary thresholds\r\n\r\nThe most concrete next step based on the documented findings is to implement the hybrid scoring experiment (Strategy C) that was identified as the next step.\r\n\r\nLooking at the key insight:\r\n\"**Compression objective for Layer 1 is now concrete**: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\"\r\n\r\nThis suggests implementing Strategy C - the hybrid scoring approach. The file `research/CFI_COMPRESSION_SYNTHESIS.md` likely contains the experiment data and the plan for Strategy C.\r\n\r\nI should:\r\n1. Create a pulse script variation that implements Strategy C (hybrid scoring)\r\n2. Or create a new experiment file documenting the hybrid scoring algorithm\r\n3. Or update the synthesis document with the concrete scoring formula to be tested\r\n\r\nGiven that the pulse just ran and noted \"No mutations applied this cycle\", I should create a concrete experiment implementation that can be tested.\r\n\r\nThe most actionable thing would be to create an experiment script that implements the hybrid scoring formula: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n\r\nLet me create a Python script that can run this experiment on the existing pulse data.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe CFI compression experiment identified that Strategy C (hybrid scoring) is the next step, with a concrete formula: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120). This needs to be implemented and tested against the existing pulse corpus.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate a Python experiment script implementing Strategy C hybrid scoring that can be run against the existing pulse data to compare with the binary threshold results from Strategy A and B.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # Strategy C: Hybrid CFI×Freq^0.5 Scoring Experiment\r\n# Next iteration of CFI compression analysis\r\n# Based on findings from CFI_COMPRESSION_SYNTHESIS.md\r\n\r\nimport json\r\nimport re\r\nfrom collections import defaultdict\r\nfrom pathlib import Path\r\n\r\ndef calculate_hybrid_score(cfi: float, freq: int) -> float:\r\n    \"\"\"Hybrid scoring: CFI weighted by frequency (capped at 120).\r\n    \r\n    Formula: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n    - Low frequency tokens (freq < 120) get proportional credit\r\n    - High frequency tokens (freq ≥ 120) get full CFI weight\r\n    - Constant-format tokens (freq≈160, CFI≈1.0) score = 1.0 (max)\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    freq_normalized = min(1.0, freq / 120.0)\r\n    return cfi * freq_normalized\r\n\r\ndef analyze_hybrid_tokens(pulses_dir: str, threshold: float = 0.3) -> dict:\r\n    \"\"\"Analyze tokens using hybrid scoring.\"\"\"\r\n    token_stats = defaultdict(lambda: {'count': 0, 'positions': []})\r\n    \r\n    pulses_path = Path(pulses_dir)\r\n    for pulse_file in sorted(pulses_path.glob('pulse_*.md'))[:200]:\r\n        content = pulse_file.read_text()\r\n        tokens = re.findall(r'\\S+', content)\r\n        for pos, token in enumerate(tokens):\r\n            token_stats[token]['count'] += 1\r\n            token_stats[token]['positions'].append(pos)\r\n    \r\n    # Calculate CFI and hybrid scores\r\n    n_pulses = len(list(pulses_path.glob('pulse_*.md'))[:200])\r\n    results = []\r\n    \r\n    for token, stats in token_stats.items():\r\n        freq = stats['count']\r\n        cfi = freq / n_pulses\r\n        hybrid_score = calculate_hybrid_score(cfi, freq)\r\n        \r\n        results.append({\r\n            'token': token,\r\n            'freq': freq,\r\n            'cfi': cfi,\r\n            'hybrid_score': hybrid_score,\r\n            'above_threshold': hybrid_score >= threshold\r\n        })\r\n    \r\n    results.sort(key=lambda x: x['hybrid_score'], reverse=True)\r\n    return {\r\n        'threshold': threshold,\r\n        'n_pulses': n_pulses,\r\n        'n_tokens': len(results),\r\n        'above_threshold': sum(1 for r in results if r['above_threshold']),\r\n        'top_tokens': results[:50]\r\n    }\r\n\r\nif __name__ == '__main__':\r\n    import sys\r\n    pulses_dir = sys.argv[1] if len(sys.argv) > 1 else '.'\r\n    result = analyze_hybrid_tokens(pulses_dir)\r\n    print(json.dumps(result, indent=2))\r\nfile: experiments/strategy_c_hybrid_scoring.py\r\n```\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 13:05:36\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774371997895}}
